We need the strict checks to correctly detect filename case changes and avoid problems with symlinks, so we can't take this PR as-is; you can see that it breaks the integration tests on platforms with case insensitive filesystems.

I think what you really want is this diff:

```
diff --git a/fbcode/watchman/FileSystem.h b/fbcode/watchman/FileSystem.h
--- a/fbcode/watchman/FileSystem.h
+++ b/fbcode/watchman/FileSystem.h
@@ -63,6 +63,7 @@
   static inline OpenFileHandleOptions openDir() {
     OpenFileHandleOptions opts;
     opts.readContents = 1;
+    opts.strictNameChecks = false;
     opts.followSymlinks = 1;
     return opts;
   }
```

which turns off the checks for the non-strict opendir.  I think this was an oversight on my part, based on this being missing here and being redundantly turned on in the strict flavor of the options method. Can you try this out and let me know if that resolves the issue for you?

